.SH NAME
HTMLTableRowElement.rowIndex \- HTMLTableRowElement: rowIndex property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]rowIndex\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableRowElement\f[R] interface represents the position of a
row within the whole \f[CR]<table>\f[R].
.PP
Even when the \f[CR]<thead>\f[R], \f[CR]<tbody>\f[R], and
\f[CR]<tfoot>\f[R] elements are out of order in the HTML, browsers
render the table in the right order.
Therefore the rows count from \f[CR]<thead>\f[R] to \f[CR]<tbody>\f[R],
from \f[CR]<tbody>\f[R] to \f[CR]<tfoot>\f[R].
.SH VALUE
The index of the row, or \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if the row is not part of a
table.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example uses JavaScript to label all the row numbers in a table.
